Please help!
I have written a simple test program and my phoenix6 generated swerve doesn’t move the robot. I get print messages showing it executes but no movement

from commands2 import Command
from wpimath.geometry import Pose2d, Translation2d
from wpimath.kinematics import ChassisSpeeds
from phoenix6 import swerve


class TestDriveCommand(Command):
    def __init__(self, drivetrain):
        super().__init__()
        self.drivetrain = drivetrain
        self.addRequirements(drivetrain)
        self._drive = (
            swerve.requests.FieldCentric()
            .with_drive_request_type(
                swerve.SwerveModule.DriveRequestType.VELOCITY
            )
        )
        self.ChassisSpeeds = ChassisSpeeds(1, 1, 0)

    def execute(self):
        print(f"TestDriveCommand execute from {self.drivetrain.get_state().pose}")
        self.drivetrain.apply_request(self._drive.with_velocity_x(1))

It is called from the robot container with:

self.keyboard_goto_position_7_7.onTrue( self.test_drive)

self.testdrive is initialized in robotcontainer with:

self.test_drive = TestDriveCommand(self.drivetrain)

apply_request takes a lambda (or function) and returns a command, you can’t call it from another command.
